"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.11\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.11</span> 标题：炉、火炉、炉灶（oven）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：תַּנּוּר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：tanur)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:17\">GEN 15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:28\">EXO 7:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:4\">LEV 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:9\">LEV 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:35\">LEV 11:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:26\">LEV 26:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:11\">NEH 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:38\">NEH 12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:10\">PSA 21:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:9\">ISA 31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:10\">LAM 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:4\">HOS 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:6\">HOS 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:7\">HOS 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:19\">MAL 3:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：κλίβανος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：klibanos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:30\">MAT 6:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:28\">LUK 12:28</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\" data-image-id=\"OAI-0054_bakingoven\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" alt=\"OAI-0054_bakingoven\"></figure>火炉是用来烹煮食物的工具，由硬化的黏土或砖制成，大小和形状各异。普通家庭的火炉直径大约为50厘米（20英寸）。冬天，火炉还能够为一间小房子供暖。另参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.11.1 窑、炉 (smelting furnace, kiln)&lt;REALIA:1.11.1&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>所有文化都知道烹煮食物的工具。“火炉”一词可译为“烘烤面包的地方”或“加热食物的地方”。有些情况下，在术语简释中提供比较详细的描述会对读者有所帮助。不过，这也不是必要的，因为火炉的功能远比它的形式重要。火炉和火窑（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.11.1 窑、炉 (smelting furnace, kiln)&lt;REALIA:1.11.1&gt;</a> ）的区别主要在于大小，基本设计是相同的。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:17\">GEN 15:17</a> 中，希伯来文<em>tanur</em> 似乎指的是一种便携式火炉或火罐，一种里面装着炭的圆形陶碗。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:30\">MAT 6:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:28\">LUK 12:28</a> ：这两节经文的主旨是：上帝甚至看顾野草等用来烧火的东西，那么岂不更加看顾他的百姓吗？因此，翻译者可以不必提及烧草的地方；例如，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 没有说“丢在炉里”（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> ），英文意为“丢到火里”，而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> 则为“烧尽了”。这样的翻译尤其适合那些不用火炉烧草的文化。另外，翻译<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:19\">MAL 3:19</a> （《和》4:1）时也应考虑上述注解。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
